Officials in India say at least 20 passengers, including schoolchildren, have died in an accident in India’s Himachal Pradesh's Kullu district. Authorities say the bus fell into a gorge. Emergency workers have reached the scene and the injured are being transported to a nearby hospital. Prime Minister Narendra Modi posted on Twitter that the accident was “heart-rending” and that he hopes “those injured recover at the earliest.” Photos from the scene show a heavily damaged bus.